tors are used to perform mathematical operations like addition, subtraction, multiplication and division.There are 7 arithmetic operators in Python : Addition,Substraction,Multiplication,Division,Modulus,Exponentiation,Floor Division'),(' assignment operator in python','explain assignment operators in python','Assignment operators are used to assign values to variables. Eg: =,+=,-=,*=,/='),(' assignment operator in python','what are the assignemnt operators in python?','Assignment operators are used to assign values to variables. Eg: =,+=,-=,*=,/='),(' assignment operator in python','assignment opertors in python','Assignment operators are used to assign values to variables. Eg: =,+=,-=,*=,/='),('comparison operator in python ','explain comparison operators in python','Comparison operators are used to compare two values. Eg:==,!=,>,<,>=,<='),('comparison operator in python ','what are the comparison operators in python?','These operators compare the values on either sides of them and decide the relation among them.. Eg:==,!=,>,<,>=,<='),('comparison operator in python ','what are the comparison operators in python?','Comparison operators are used to compare two values. Eg:==,!=,>,<,>=,<='),('logical operator in python','explain logical operators in python','Logical operators are used to combine conditional statements. Logical opeartors are: AND, OR, NOT'),('logical operator in python','what are the logical operators in python?','In Python, Logical operators are used on conditional statements (either True or False). They perform Logical AND, Logical OR and Logical NOT operations.'),('logical operator in python',' logical operators in python','Logical Operators in Python are used to perform logical operations on the values of variables. The value is either true or false. We can figure out the conditions by the result of the truth values. There are mainly three types of logical operators in python : logical AND, logical OR and logical NOT. '),('while loop in python','While loop in python','In Python, While Loops is used to execute a block of statements repeatedly until a given condition is satisfied. And when the condition becomes false, the line immediately after the loop in the program is executed. While loop falls under the category of indefinite iteration. Syntax:while expression:\n    statement(s)\n'),('while loop in python','Explain while loop in python','A \"While\" Loop is used to repeat a specific block of code an unknown number of times, until a condition is met. For example, if we want to ask a user for a number between 1 and 10, we don\'t know how many times the user may enter a larger number, so we keep asking \"while the number is not between 1 and 10\". syntax: while expression:\n    statement(s)'),('while loop in python','while loop syntax in python','The while loop in Python is used to iterate over a block of code as long as the test expression (condition) is true. Syntax for while loop in python:while test_expression:\n    Body of while'),('Internal math function in python','what are the internal math functions in python','The Python interpreter has a number of functions and types built into it that are always available. Built in python math functions are: abs(),min(), max(),round(),pow()'),('Internal math function in python','Whate are the built in math functions in python.','The Python interpreter has a number of functions and types built into it that are always available. Built in python math functions are: abs(),min(), max(),round(),pow()'),('Internal math function in python','Build-in math functions in python','The Python interpreter has a number of functions and types built into it that are always available. Built in python math functions are: abs(),min(), max(),round(),pow()'),('Random module in python','What is a random module in python','The random module is a built-in module to generate the pseudo-random variables. It can be used perform some action randomly such as to get a random number, selecting a random elements from a list, shuffle elements randomly, etc. syntax: import random'),('Random module in python','Random module in python','Python defines a set of functions that are used to generate or manipulate random numbers through the random module. Functions in the random module rely on a pseudo-random number generator function random(), which generates a random float number between 0.0 and 1.0. These particular type of functions is used in a lot of games, lotteries, or any application requiring a random number generation.'),('Random module in python','What is the use of random module in python','You can generate random numbers in Python by using random module.These are pseudo-random number as the sequence of number generated depends on the seed. If the seeding value is same, the sequence will be the same.Syntax: import random'),('if else loop in python','Explain if else loop in python','The if statement alone tells us that if a condition is true it will execute a block of statements and if the condition is false it won’t. But what if we want to do something else if the condition is false. Here comes the else statement. We can use the else statement with if statement to execute a block of code when the condition is false.Syntax of if statement: if (condition):\n    # Executes this block if\n    # condition is true\nelse:\n    # Executes this block if\n    # condition is false'),('if else loop in python','if else loop in python','The if..else statement evaluates test expression and will execute the body of if only when the test condition is True . If the condition is False , the body of else is executed. Indentation is used to separate the blocks.Syntax of if statement: if (condition):\n    # Executes this block if\n    # condition is true\nelse:\n    # Executes this block if\n    # condition is false'),('if else loop in python','if else statemnet in python','An if else Python statement evaluates whether an expression is true or false. If a condition is true, the “if” statement executes. Otherwise, the “else” statement executes. Python if else statements help coders control the flow of their programs.Syntax of if statement: if (condition):\n    # Executes this block if\n    # condition is true\nelse:\n    # Executes this block if\n    # condition is false'),('object oriented programming in python','Is python an object oriented programming language','Python is a great programming language that supports OOP.Object-oriented programming is a programming paradigm based on the concept of \"objects\", which can contain data and code: data in the form of fields, and code, in the form of procedures.Major principles of object-oriented programming system are given below: Class,Object,Method,Inheritance,Polymorphism,Data Abstraction,Encapsulation'),('object oriented programming in python','python oop\'s concepts','Python is also an object-oriented language since its beginning. It allows us to develop applications using an Object-Oriented approach. In Python, we can easily create and use classes and objects.The oops concept focuses on writing the reusable code.Major principles of object-oriented programming system are given below: Class,Object,Method,Inheritance,Polymorphism,Data Abstraction,Encapsulation'),('object oriented programming in python','object oriented programming concepts in python','Object-oriented programming (OOP) is a programming paradigm based on the concept of \"objects\", which can contain data and code: data in the form of fields (often known as attributes or properties), and code, in the form of procedures (often known as methods).Major principles of object-oriented programming system are given below: Class,Object,Method,Inheritance,Polymorphism,Data Abstraction,Encapsulation'),('class in python','What is a class in python?','A Class is like an object constructor, or a \"blueprint\" for creating objects.To create a class, use the keyword class. Syntax: class MyClass:\n '),('class in python','Define class in pytho